<br>
Just had an idea driving home from work. Everyone is aware of all the controversy with warrior aggro, and there are probably many ideas to solve the problem. Here is my idea. (BTW I have had SK to lvl 59, war to lvl 52)<br>
<br>
1. First, DO NOT NERF knights please. Nobody needs this. Right now warriors are mad because of how easily knights can gain and hold aggro. This make perfect sense to me - think if you were in a group and you were facing 2 mobs, one which was pure melee and one which was meleeing and casting, which would your group try to kill first? Obviously the one who was meleeing and casting. Thus, it makes perfect sense that the monsters would focus there attention on the knight over the warrior. Lets just accept this as the way it is. The drawback is that knights have less HP/mitigation, and warriors have defensive and will be preferred for tanking raid mobs most of the time.<br>
<br>
2. So where does this leave warriors who are not in a raid? LFG a lot of the time. So, rather than nerfing knights (either by reducing their aggro generating abilities or increasing warriors aggro - both of which would lead to kngiths being LFG again), lets give the warriors a suitable role in an exp group outside of being the MT. What would this role be? Simple - increase their damage output. Make warriors a viable DPS option in an exp group. So now you can have a paladin tanking for aggro control, and add the warrior for pure DPS. If we can increase warrior DPS to come close to ranger/bst/monk, then they have a job to do and will be able to get groups again.<br>
<br>
3. My suggestion is that SOE inpliment a skill-based ability which would be sort of like rogue backstab - I call it Bloodlust. You would train your 1pt in bloodlust and get a hot button. Every time you press the hot button, it would increase your chacnes of getting a critical on your next attack by X%. Lets say for simplicity that the % critical would be directly proportional to your level. So a level 20 warrior would have a 20% chance of criting on next attack, and a level 60 warrior would have a 60% chance. The refresh rate would be determine by skill level. Thus, as a warrior levels, he will do increasingly more damage from criting, both in terms of % chance of criting and rate of criting. This would seriously increase their DPS and make them viable in any group, even if a knight was going to tank. Of course the numbers would have to be worked out so they are not overpowered, but you get the idea.<br>
<br>
4. The caveat would be that the bloodlust ability would NOT work in /disc defensive mode, and this makes sense since you are focusing on defense, not offense in that mode.<br>
<br>
5. So, in realistic situations (1) raid - warriors are already fine in this situation with /disc defensive (2) exp group with knight - warrior uses /bloodlust skill to become DPSer for group (3) exp group war tanking - war still can't get/hold aggro as well as knight, but with icnreased damage output from /bloodlust skill the additional DPS will certainly help to hold more aggro than currently.<br>
<br>
<br>
All in all, I think this may be a way of helping warriors out without hurting any other classes. What do you guys think?<br>
<br>
Ras<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
